            <h3>Tenure-track Positions</h3>
            <p>Department of Theoretical Physics at the Wrocław University of Science and Technology expects to have openings for tenure-track positions under <a href="https://ncn.gov.pl/ogloszenia/konkursy/sonata-bis10?language=en"><b>the SONATA BIS</b></a> program of the National Science Centre <a href="https://www.ncn.gov.pl/?language=en"><b>NCN</b></a>. The call for applications will soon be open. </p>
            <p>The planned application period is mid-September 2021. Eligible candidates are early career researchers between 4 and 12 years after completion of the PhD degree. This is a broad call in the fields encompassing  active materials, applications of machine learning in physics, complex systems, light-matter interactions, non-equilibrium quantum matter, quantum computing, quantum phases of matter.</p>
            <p>The application procedure assumes a three-step evaluation. In the first step the applicants should send their CV, a research plan and three reference letters to <b>wppt.kft@pwr.edu.pl</b> by the end of April. Please include your name and “SONATA BIS” in the title.</p>
            <p>Successful applicants will be contacted shortly afterwards to write the grant proposal, which will be evaluated in the second step of the application procedure. In the third and final step the candidates will be invited for an interview to the National Science Centre located in Cracow, Poland. We stress that the university does not handle the grant applications but will provide necessary guidance and administrative help throughout the process.</p>
        </div>
